-- OTE May Sell a Unit to Fund Debt-Servicing, Naftemporiki Reports
-- B y   P a u l   T u g w e l l
-- 2012-04-12T09:42:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-12/ote-may-sell-a-unit-to-fund-debt-servicing-naftemporiki-reports.html
Hellenic Telecommunications
Organization SA (HTO) , known as OTE, may sell one of its units in
Albania, Bulgaria or  Romania  to obtain money for servicing debt,
 Naftemporiki  reported, without citing anyone.  OTE, which faces a funding shortfall of 500 million to 700
million euros ($656 million to $919 million) will make decisions
on how to increase liquidity and cut operating costs by the end
of the first half, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Tugwell at 
 ptugwell1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jerrold Colten at 
 jcolten@bloomberg.net  